Sentencas: The microstructure, elements distribution, and crystallinity of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) and BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-delta (BZY) nanofibers prepared by electrospinning method are systematically characterized.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ and BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ Electrospun Nanofiber Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of the single cell with the cathode of nanofiber microstructure is tested by compared with the traditional powder materials.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ and BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ Electrospun Nanofiber Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results of electrochemical measurement manifest that the overall performance of the cells is improved greatly by the cathode with nanofibers.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ and BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ Electrospun Nanofiber Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: At the operating temperature of 700 degrees C, the peak power density is 1105 mW cm(-2) and the polarization resistance is 0.041 omega cm(2), much better than the cells with powder cathode.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ and BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ Electrospun Nanofiber Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The nanofiber cathode has excellent permeability and faster charge transfer rate due to its porous network structure, uniform diameter, and small grain size.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ and BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ Electrospun Nanofiber Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Three-phase boundaries and reaction rate in cathode are increased, and thus the stability and electrochemical performance of individual cells are improved.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ and BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ Electrospun Nanofiber Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This study not only expands the application of electrospinning in the field of energy, but also provides more methods to prepare high-quality electrode materials for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ and BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ Electrospun Nanofiber Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
